        eng: 'Research on Nutritional Components of Plant-Based Foods In recent years, the nutritional components of plant-based foods have been attracting attention. In this study, we examined chemical methods used to quantify the essential nutrients in plant-based foods. The results of the study revealed that among plant-based foods containing moisture, protein, fat, minerals and other nutrients, soy products (such as soy meat) contain the most essential nutrients. It was also found that other products such as nut products (such as nut butter) and wheat products (such as wheat bread) also contain a lot of essential nutrients. From these results, it is possible that plant-based foods contain a lot of essential nutrients and further precise quantification of nutritional components is expected in the future. ',
