        eng: 'Yokohama is one of the largest cities in Japan and has many industrial facilities and international ports. The city was developed during the Meiji period and has developed as one of the most important industrial regions among Japanese cities. Today, it continues to grow as a global trading hub. Geographically, it is located southeast of Tokyo. There are many cultural facilities within the city and tourists often visit them. Major tourist spots include Kannai and Motomachi, etc. There are many Japanese cultures in Yokohama. In recent years, there are also international schools and old historical buildings. The climate of Yokohama can be divided into four seasons: spring (March to May), summer (June to August), autumn (September to November) and winter (December to February). The climate is warm and there is a tendency for rain to fall throughout the year. Therefore, residents should not forget to bring rain gear with them. Yokohama is an international city and there is also an international community here. In particular, in recent years, the number of foreign income earners has increased sharply, and there is a tendency for the proportion of foreign income earners to be high as well. Along with this, it can be said that English has begun to be widely used as well. ',
