        eng: "Walking through a village in the mountains under a red sky, the grassy fields swayed in the damp wind, and the sun shone brightly. As I walked, I couldn't help but smile. This was the most gentle and tender atmosphere I had ever experienced. Looking around, there were small houses lined up, low and old buildings, but they exuded a peaceful atmosphere that reminded me of good old days. The people of the village were also kind, and as I walked with them, I listened to their stories. I arrived at the center of the village and decided to take a break in a small square. Around the square were small wooden buildings and on the first floor there were ice cream and juice shops. In the center was a large old tree from which you could see the townscape around it. As I looked at the surrounding townscape, I was moved by the beauty of the setting sun and the quiet atmosphere of the village. At this time, I felt a feeling of peace and comfort spreading in my heart. ",
