        eng: "She slowly started to walk and began to doubt herself. Until now, she hadn't thought about what she had done. She hadn't looked back on her life. She felt that was the cause of the change this time. Would she have the will to face whatever hardships come her way? Amidst her questioning heart, a small ray of hope shone in. She returned to her room and decided to take a break. Lying on the bed with her eyes closed, she remembered something; it was from her high school days, when a friend gave her courage. Her friend gave her courage and encouraged her to keep going with all her might. As she gazed upon the memories, she gradually began to understand the emotion that was rising from deep within her heart - courage...the power to keep getting up no matter how many times you fail...the power to use your past experiences and walk down a new path...the courage to stand up again...the power to live positively from now on...the power of conviction... As she continued thinking, she made one decision - 'From today, you will become a positive person.'",
