        eng: " I looked up at the night sky, which was getting darker. I felt like I had forgotten where I was, what I was doing, and what I wanted. It was a feeling of being a lonely and small existence in this deep and vast space of the night sky. Under the pitch-black night sky, I felt as if I was being asked about the meaning of my existence. 'Everyone lives alone,' I thought. It was a painful and anxious feeling. There are times when we strive to gain something, and times when we lose something.I thought it was important to accept our emotions at that time and live with them. Today's me is today's me, and tomorrow's me is tomorrow's me - I thought that I should live in the present with this thought in mind. When I tried to organize the chaotic thoughts in my head by taking a deep breath, a wind started to flow in the space. The sound of the wind echoed near my ears, and I felt strongly encouraged from within. 'Let's go in the direction of where the wind blows,'I thought. As soon as I started walking guided by my heart, it felt like light was shining from deep inside my chest.",
