        eng: "At a slow pace, Dad entered the study room. The room was enveloped in a mysterious atmosphere that changed from darkness to darkness. When I looked at the cover of the old books lined up on the bookshelf, I could see the classics that Dad had accumulated over the years. There were also literary works transmitted from ancient times and historical notes, and it made me feel his years when I could see them all at once. In the corner of the room, there was a small table. On top of it was a small oil lamp and I could see a faint blue light inside it. On top of the table were also several old manuscripts, some with red covers that made me imagine treasures, and some with yellowed covers that made me imagine something else. 'Please read this,' he said, so I started to open one of the old manuscripts in my hand. The contents of the old manuscript were very interesting; it told stories about Japan's climate and people's lives in the Middle Ages. As I read it, I felt the difference between today's life and at the same time realized that human beings' fundamental aspects remain unchanged. ",
